# Google Drive MCP Server Settings
# Use this file to configure the Google Drive MCP server for Claude Desktop
#
# Format:
# SETTING_NAME=value
#
# Required Settings:
# -----------------
# Note: This MCP server requires OAuth authentication rather than API keys.
# You will need to follow the authentication process described in the README.
# The server will save credentials to .gdrive-server-credentials.json
#
# Optional Settings:
# -----------------
# DOCKER_IMAGE - Docker image name and tag (default: mcp/gdrive:latest)
# RESTART_CLAUDE - Whether to restart Claude Desktop if it's running (true/false, default: true)
# CREDENTIALS_PATH - Path to the credentials file (default: .gdrive-server-credentials.json)
# GCP_OAUTH_KEYS_PATH - Path to the GCP OAuth keys file (default: gcp-oauth.keys.json)
#
# Examples:
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/gdrive:custom
# RESTART_CLAUDE=false
# CREDENTIALS_PATH=/path/to/credentials.json
# GCP_OAUTH_KEYS_PATH=/path/to/oauth-keys.json
#
# Default settings (uncomment and modify as needed):
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/gdrive:latest
# RESTART_CLAUDE=true
# CREDENTIALS_PATH=.gdrive-server-credentials.json
# GCP_OAUTH_KEYS_PATH=gcp-oauth.keys.json
